************************
SUMMARY OF DATA FILES
************************

1. List of data files
	Filename: Average Precipitation and Mean Temperature of Nepal for Different Seasons During the Reference Period(1981-2010)
	Short description: Precipitation Average in mm and %, Temperature in degree Celsius for Winter, Pre-moonsoon, Monsoon and Post-monsoon. 
	
	Filename: Change in Cold Days (%) for Districts of Nepal from the Reference Period (1981-2010)
	Short description: Change in Mean Annual Cold Days in  for RCP4.5 and RCP8.5 Scenarios for 77 districts of Nepal expressed in %. The future data hinted the likely decrease of Cold Days in each 
	scenarios.

	Filename: Change in Cold Nights (%) for Districts of Nepal from the Reference Period (1981-2010)
	Short description: Change in Cold Nights expressed in % for RCP4.5 and RCP8.5 Scenarios for 77 districts of Nepal on annual basis. The future data hinted the likely decrease of Cold Nights in each 
	scenarios.

	Filename: Change in Cold Spell Duration Index (CSDI) (%) for Districts of Nepal from the Reference Period (1981-2010)
	Short description: Change in Cold Speel Duration Index expressed in % for RCP4.5 and RCP8.5 Scenarios for 77 districts of Nepal on annual basis. The future data hinted the likely decrease of Cold
	Spell Duration in each scenarios.
	
	Filename: Change in Consecutive Dry Days (CDD) (%) for districts of Nepal from the reference period (1981-2010)
	Short description: In the medium-term and long-term period, CDD is likely to increase in the whole of Nepal for RCP4.5, whereas it may slightly decrease for RCP8.5. 
	
	Filename: Change in Consecutive Wet Days (CWD) (%) for Districts of Nepal from the Reference Period (1981-2010)
	Short description: In the medium-term and long-term period, CWD is likely to decrease in the whole of Nepal for RCP4.5, whereas it may slightly increase for RCP8.5.
	
	Filename: Change in Extreme Wet Days (P99) (%) for Districts of Nepal from the Reference Period (1981-2010)
	Short description: Proected data in expressed in change percentage in annual extreme wet days where the precipitation is greater than 99th percentile. The projection data provides alerting
	information as increase in extreme wet days implies more occurance of flash floods and other water induced hazards like landslide. The dataset implies in both medium and long term for scenarios 4.5
	and 8.5 extreme wet days is likely to increasae.
	
	Filename :Change in No. of Rainy Days (%) for Districts of Nepal from the Reference Period (1981-2010)
	Short description: In the future periods, the number of rainy days is likely to decrease all over Nepal. The dataset provides data in change in annual rainy days expressed in percentage for 77 
	districts of Nepal.
	
	Filename: Change in Temperature (°C) for Districts of Nepal from the Reference period (1981-2010)
	Short description: Dataset for the future projection under of temperature scenario rcp4.5 and rcp8.5 in medium and long term. The temperature change is positive under both medium and long-term 
	scenarios
	
	Filename:Change in Very Wet Days (P95) (%) for Districts of Nepal from the Reference Period (1981-2010)
	Short description: Change in annual very wet days when the precipitation is over 95th percentile. Provided data for 77 districts. Data for medium-term and long-term under rcp4.5 and rcp8.5 scenarios
	
	Filename: Change in Warm Days (%) for Districts of Nepal from the Reference Period (1981-2010)
	Short description:  Dataste about percentage change in warm days when the maximum temperature is higher than the 90th percentile of the reference maximum temperature for the medium-term and long-
	term periods of RCP4.5 and RCP8.5 across 77 districts in Nepal.
	
	Filename: Change in Warm Nights (%) for Districts of Nepal from the Reference Period (1981-2010)
	Short Description: Dataset for percentage change in warm nights when the minimum temperature ishigher than the 90th percentile of the reference minimum temperature for the medium-term and the 
	longterm periods of RCP4.5 and RCP8.5 across 77 districts in Nepal
	
	Filename: Change in Warm Spell Duration Index (WSDI) (%) for Districts of Nepal from the Reference Period (1981-2010)
	Short Description: Dataset for percentage change in warm spell duration index (WSDI) for RCP4.5 and RCP8.5 scenarios when the daily maximum temperature is higher than the 90th percentile of the 
	maximum temperature of the reference period for at least six consecutive days across 77 districts in Nepal.
	
	Filename: Multi-Model Ensemble Mean of Change in Temperature(°C) in the Medium-Term and the Long-Term Period for Different Seasons
	Short description: Dataset for change in average annual precipitation and mean temperature for winter, pre-monsoon, monsoon and post-monsoon
	
	Filename: Multi-model Ensemble Mean of Change in Temperature(°C) in the Medium-Term and the Long-term period for Different Regions of Nepal
	Short description: Dataset for change in average annual mean temperature for different physiographic zones by name High Mountain, Middle Mountain, Hill, Siwalik and Terai
	
	Filename: Multi-Model Ensemble Mean of Change in Precipitation(mm) in the Medium-Term and the Long-Term Period for Different Regions of Nepal
	Short description: Dataset for change in average annual precipitation for different physiographic zones by name High Mountain, Middle Mountain, Hill, Siwalik and Terai
	
	Filename: Multi-model Ensemble Mean of Change in Precipitation and Temperature in the Medium-Term and the Long-Term for the whole Nepal
	Short description: Dataset for percantage change in average annual precipitation and temperature and mean temperature for whole Nepal.
	
		 
	

